Interesting fact that one you can build your own electronic stuff, it means that there is a lot of technologic wisdom among the population and not only common usage of devices such as in western countries

I think technology and products produced in Shenzen can be said as one of innovation product because Shenzen is the first city ever that named as National Self-Innovation Demonstration Zone. shenzhen has long placed innovation as a leading strategy in its development by using innovation to improve the quality of both economic and industrial development. 

1. They have open source and they create new/latest product innovation and it
is not solely for the market but it is to gain and develop new ideas for high and
middle technology in the new era. - For example, from the documentary video itself they innovates phone from previous or new produced phone to different specification according to their customer
requirement. The most surprising part is they already succeed in imitates
phone that are not yet release in the market. Fast pace technology helps them
to growth new innovation faster than any advanced country. As they also create no just for the market but for their ideas and hobby. 

2. They have everything you need to get things done. Every equipment are
available in the store. If in the west you need approximately 9 to 12 months to
get equipment shipment to fully finish your prototype but in china only 3
months you can get things done. As fast as lightning or even faster than that. -For example, in Huaqiangbei there is more than 800-900 stores inside the
building itself. As Malaysian, if you think Plaza Lowyat have every technology
you need imagine living in China specifically in Shenzhen and Huaqiangbei. On top of that, regardless any age you are, you can create new innovation based on what is in the market. They teach kids at age of 8 years old to start building and learning to use coding/programming. One of the kid managed to create one software to remind his mom to pick up the key whenever she is going out. Every day is a new day of innovation product produce at there.

Anyone coming here should venture into the hills behind the gold coast. Its truly paradise. You need to hire a camper van and spend a few days driving through them. Mt warning just across the nsw border is truly magnificent

I was there 3 months ago for 2 weeks and I couldn't agree more about Gold Coast's beauty! Broadbeach, Surfers Paradise, Burleigh Heads and Coolangatta are just stunning places to go. I also went to O'Reilly's near the Mount Tambourine and the place was heavenly beautiful. Thank you for making a good video of the Gold Coast. I cannot wait to go there again someday!

Nicely done.  One fact change.  @ 3:34  The reason Houston was selected as the site for Mission Control.  Not the weather - almost all NASA activities are indoors.  LBJ brokered a deal with Humble (now ExxonMobil) to write-off an old oil field ( Clear Lake ) to the federal government to become the new site for NASA Mission Control.

The most amazing and magical city. Rare to find a one stop city for culture, art, glamour, history, cuisine and the welcoming warmth of family. Viva Mexico!

I've lived in Canada and USA, but when I went to Mexico city for the fist time it felt magical and people treated me like family. The city has a Mixture of Indigenous, Spanish and French culture which makes it so unique.
